<text>Opening a new window from a hyperlink

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

Sometimes you want to have the reader open a new window when clicking a hyperlink, to show something that is best placed outside the current page. You want to be able to specify the size and the location of the pop-up window, and you hardly want the reader to go anywhere from the pop-up window if the content displayed in it is a reference to the content in the original window. 

You can specify a number of properties for the pop-up window to be opened from a hyperlink, including:

   left  -  Defines the distance between the left side of the window and the left border of the screen.
   top  -  Defines the distance between the top side of the window and the top border of the screen.
   width  -  Defines the width of the window.
   height  -  Defines the height of the window.
   resizable  -  Determines whether or not the popup window will be resizable.
   toolbar  -  Determines whether or not to keep the toolbar
   menubar  -  Determines whether or not to keep the menubar.
   statusbar  -  Determines whether or not to keep the statusbar. 
   fullscreen  -  Determines whether the window should be in fullscreen mode (not supported yet).

These properties can be specified with the dialog window that comes up when you click the &quot;Advanced&quot; button in the Hyperlink Dialog, as is shown below: (The &quot;Advanced&quot; button is disabled if the hyperlink will not open up a new window.)

  
[This is a screenshot.]

(These properties are similar to those you can specify using Javascript for a browser, if you know.)

Examples: 

The following link opens up a new window with the same size as this one and has toolbar and the menubar on it:

&#10154; link 1

The following link opens up a new window with the same size as this one without the toolbar and the menubar on it:

&#10154; link 2

The following link opens up a new non-resizable window with a size (400x400) without the toolbar, the menubar and the status bar on it:

&#10154; link 3

When you design a hyperlink that can open up a new window, you often want to also place a &quot;Close&quot; button in the new window that the user can click to close it. You can insert such a button by chosing the menu &quot;Insert&gt;Activity Controller&gt;Activity Button&quot;, and on the dialog window, choose the &quot;Close this page&quot; action.

 
Note: Unfortunately, you cannot customize the popup window if the hyperlink is a HTML one embedded in a text box, a color bar, or a multiple choice.
 

